Template: led-matrix/led-rows
Type: string
Default: 64
Description: Rows per panel (--led-rows)
 Number of rows on each LED matrix panel.
 Common values are 16, 32, 64.

Template: led-matrix/led-cols
Type: string
Default: 64
Description: Columns per panel (--led-cols)
 Number of columns on each LED matrix panel.
 Common values are 32, 64.

Template: led-matrix/led-chain
Type: string
Default: 2
Description: Number of chained panels (--led-chain)
 How many panels are daisy-chained together per parallel chain.

Template: led-matrix/led-parallel
Type: string
Default: 2
Description: Number of parallel chains (--led-parallel)
 How many parallel chains of panels are connected.

Template: led-matrix/led-slowdown-gpio
Type: string
Default: 3
Description: GPIO slowdown value (--led-slowdown-gpio)
 Slows down GPIO writes to avoid visual artefacts.
 Recommended value is 3 for Raspberry Pi 3 Model B,
 2 for Raspberry Pi 4. Leave blank to use library default.

Template: led-matrix/extra-opts
Type: string
Default:
Description: Extra matrix options
 Any additional command-line flags for the matrix controller,
 e.g. --led-brightness=80 --led-rgb-sequence=RBG.
 Leave blank to skip.

Template: led-matrix/spotify-enable
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Enable Spotify Plugin?
 The Spotify Plugin displays the album art of the song currently
 playing on your Spotify account. Requires a Spotify Developer
 account with a registered application.

Template: led-matrix/spotify-client-id
Type: string
Default:
Description: Spotify Client ID
 The Client ID from your Spotify Developer application.
 Leave blank to configure later.

Template: led-matrix/spotify-client-secret
Type: password
Default:
Description: Spotify Client Secret
 The Client Secret from your Spotify Developer application.

Template: led-matrix/auto-update-enable
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Enable automatic updates?
 The LED Matrix Controller can automatically check for and install
 updates from GitHub releases. This keeps your system up to date
 with the latest features and fixes.

Template: led-matrix/auto-update-interval
Type: select
Default: 24
Choices: 6, 12, 24, 48, 168
Description: Update check interval (hours)
 How often to check for new releases.
 6 = every 6 hours (bleeding edge)
 12 = every 12 hours
 24 = every 24 hours (recommended)
 48 = every 48 hours
 168 = every week
